In [7]:
def RSI(stock, column='adjclose', period=14):
    # Wilder's RSI
    close = stock[column]
    delta = close.diff() 
    up, down = delta.copy(), delta.copy()

    up[up < 0] = 0
    down[down > 0] = 0
    
    # Calculate the exponential moving averages (EWMA)
    roll_up = up.ewm(com=period - 1, adjust=False).mean()
    roll_down = down.ewm(com=period - 1, adjust=False).mean().abs()
    
    # Calculate RS based on exponential moving average (EWMA)
    rs = roll_up / roll_down   # relative strength =  average gain/average loss

    rsi = 100-(100/(1+rs))
    
    return rsi
In [8]:
StartDate = dt.date(2020,1,1)
EndDate = today.date()

i = 0

data5 = {}
for sss in List:
    Security = sss[0]
    data5[i] = yf.get_data(Security, start_date=StartDate, end_date=EndDate, index_as_date=False, interval='1d')
    
    data5[i]['50dExpAve'] = data5[i]['high'].ewm(span=50, adjust=False).mean()
    data5[i]['100dExpAve'] = data5[i]['high'].ewm(span=100, adjust=False).mean()
    
    data5[i]['12dExpAve'] = data5[i]['high'].ewm(span=12, adjust=False).mean()
    data5[i]['26dExpAve'] = data5[i]['high'].ewm(span=26, adjust=False).mean()
    data5[i]['MACD'] = data5[i]['12dExpAve'] - data5[i]['26dExpAve']
    data5[i]['signal'] = data5[i]['MACD'].ewm(span=9, adjust=False).mean()
    data5[i]['bar1'] = data5[i]['MACD'] - data5[i]['signal']
    
    data5[i]['RSI'] = RSI(data5[i], period=14)

    i = i + 1

def BokehPlotTemplate(fig):
    global BokehTools
    fig.background_fill_color = '#cccccc'
    fig.background_fill_alpha = .4
    
    fig.xaxis.axis_line_color = 'white'
    fig.yaxis.axis_line_color = 'white'
    fig.xgrid.grid_line_color = 'white'
    fig.ygrid.grid_line_color = 'white'
    fig.yaxis.minor_tick_line_color = None

    fig.xaxis.formatter=DatetimeTickFormatter(
        hours=["%d %b %y"],
        days=["%d %b %y"],
        months=["%d %b %y"],
        years=["%d %b %y"],
    )

    fig.title.text_font_size = '12pt'
    fig.title.align = 'center'

    fig.yaxis.axis_label = 'Stock Price (USD)'
    
    legend = Legend(items=[
    ])
    fig.add_layout(legend, 'right')

def PlotStock1(i):
    
    fig5 = bkplt.figure(title = 'Title', x_axis_type='datetime', tools='', plot_width=900, plot_height=500)
    BokehPlotTemplate(fig5)

    source = ColumnDataSource(data5[i])
    fig5.line(x='date', y='high', legend_label='intra-day high', line_color='red', source=source)
    fig5.line(x='date', y='50dExpAve', legend_label='50-day Average', line_color='blue', source=source)
    fig5.line(x='date', y='100dExpAve', legend_label='100-day Average', line_color='green', source=source)

    fig5.title.text = List[i][0]
    fig5.x_range = DataRange1d(start=PlotFromDate, end=PlotToDate)
      
    hover = HoverTool(
        tooltips=[
            ('date', '@date{%d %b %y}'), # {%d %b %y}
            ('high', '@high{$0.2f}'),
            ('50d ave', '@50dExpAve{$0.2f}'),
            ('100d ave', '@100dExpAve{$0.2f}'),
        ],
        formatters={
            '@date'        : 'datetime', # use 'datetime' formatter for '@date' field
            #'@{adj close}' : 'printf',   # use 'printf' formatter for '@{adj close}' field
                                     # use default 'numeral' formatter for other fields
        },
    )
    #fig.tools = 'box_zoom, crosshair, reset'
    fig5.add_tools(BoxZoomTool(), CrosshairTool(), ResetTool())
    fig5.add_tools(hover)

    tab = Panel(child=fig5, title=List[i][0])
    return tab

i = 0
tabs = []
for sss in List:
    Security = sss[0]
    tab = PlotStock1(i)
    tabs.append(tab)
    i = i+1
bkplt.show(Tabs(tabs=tabs))

    fig4.xaxis.visible = False
    
    fig41 = bkplt.figure(title = 'Title', x_axis_type='datetime', tools='', plot_width=800, plot_height=250)
    BokehPlotTemplate(fig41)

    source = ColumnDataSource(data5[i])

    fig41.line(x='date', y='signal', legend_label='MACD Signal', line_color='orange', source=source)
    
    fig41.vbar(x='date', top='bar1', legend_label='MACD Histogram', line_color='blue', line_width=0, fill_color='blue',\
               fill_alpha=0.5, width=dt.timedelta(days=1), source=source)
    
    fig41.title.text = ''
    #fig41.x_range = DataRange1d(start=PlotFromDate, end=PlotToDate)
    fig41.x_range = fig4.x_range


    #fig41.xaxis.fixed_location = 0
    fig41.yaxis.axis_label = 'MACD'
    
    zero_span = Span(location=0.0, dimension='width', line_color='black', line_width=1, line_dash='dashed')
    fig41.renderers.extend([zero_span])
    
    
    
    hover = HoverTool(
    tooltips=[

                                     # use default 'numeral' formatter for other fields
        },
    )
    #fig.tools = 'box_zoom, crosshair, reset'
    fig4.add_tools(BoxZoomTool(), CrosshairTool(), ResetTool())
    fig4.add_tools(hover)
    
    
    
    hover = HoverTool(
    tooltips=[
        ('date', '@date{%d %b %y}'), # {%d %b %y}
        ('MACD', '@MACD{$0.2f}'),
        ('MACD Signal', '@signal{$0.2f}'),
        ('Diff', '@bar1{$0.2f}'),
        ],
    formatters={
        '@date'        : 'datetime', # use 'datetime' formatter for '@date' field
        #'@{adj close}' : 'printf',   # use 'printf' formatter for '@{adj close}' field

def BokehPlotTemplate2(fig):
    global BokehTools
    fig.background_fill_color = '#cccccc'
    fig.background_fill_alpha = .4
    
    fig.xaxis.axis_line_color = 'white'
    fig.yaxis.axis_line_color = 'white'
    fig.xgrid.grid_line_color = 'white'
    fig.ygrid.grid_line_color = 'white'
    fig.yaxis.minor_tick_line_color = None

    fig.xaxis.formatter=DatetimeTickFormatter(
        hours=["%d %b %y"],
        days=["%d %b %y"],
        months=["%d %b %y"],
        years=["%d %b %y"],
    )

    fig.title.text_font_size = '12pt'
    fig.title.align = 'center'

    fig.yaxis.axis_label = 'RSI'  
    fig.title.text = 'Relative Strength Index (RSI)'
    
    legend = Legend(items=[
    ])
    fig.add_layout(legend, 'right')
#    fig.legend.location = 'top_left'
    
    hover = HoverTool(
        tooltips=[
            ('date', '@date{%d %b %y}'), # {%d %b %y}
            ('sec', '@ticker'),
            ('RSI', '@RSI{0.2f}'),
        ],
        formatters={
            '@date'        : 'datetime', # use 'datetime' formatter for '@date' field
            #'@{adj close}' : 'printf',   # use 'printf' formatter for '@{adj close}' field
                                     # use default 'numeral' formatter for other fields
        },
    )
    #fig.tools = 'box_zoom, crosshair, reset'

In [ ]:

Moving average convergence divergence (MACD) is calculated by subtracting the 26-period exponential moving average (EMA) from the 12-period EMA. MACD triggers technical signals when it crosses above (to buy) or below (to sell) its signal line. The speed of crossovers is also taken as a signal of a market is overbought or oversold. MACD helps investors understand whether the bullish or bearish movement in the price is strengthening or weakening.
